<h4>Sizes</h4>
<p>The default size uses 36pt for the number and 40px for an icon. A large stat uses 48pt for the number and 64px for an icon. Both size variations use 18pt for body text and 20pt for titles.</p>
{% call components.example(palette='light') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-sizes.svg' | url }}" alt="Examples of stat in the default and large sizes"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 752px;">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

<h4>Configurations/variants</h4>
<p>An icon can be added as the first element in a statistic.</p>
<p><rh-cta>
    <a href="/get-started/icon-library/">Learn more about using icons</a> 
</rh-cta>
</p>
{% call components.example(palette='light') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <rh-stat icon="rh-telecom-vertical">
            <span slot="statistic">80%</span>
            <span>of Fortune Global 500 telecom companies<sup>1</sup></span>
        </rh-stat>
    </div>
{%- endcall %}
<p>A call to action can be added as the last element in a statistic.</p>
{% call components.example(palette='light') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <rh-stat>
            <span slot="statistic">80%</span>
            <span>of Fortune Global 500 telecom companies<sup>1</sup></span>
            <rh-cta slot="cta">
                <a href="#">Learn more</a>
            </rh-cta>
        </rh-stat>
    </div>
{%- endcall %}
<p>A stat can be placed inside a card.</p>
{% call components.example(palette='medium') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-config-in-card.svg' | url }}" alt="Example of a stat centered in a card"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 406px;">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

<h4>Alignment</h4>
<p>All content in a stat should use the same alignment. Currently all stat content is centered.</p>
{% call components.example(palette='light') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <rh-stat>
            <span slot="title">More than</span>
            <span slot="statistic">90%</span>
            <span>of Fortune 500 companies rely on Red Hat<sup>1</sup></span>
        </rh-stat>
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

{%- endcall %}


{% call components.section("Usage") -%}

<h4 style="margin-top: -4px;">Layout</h4>

<p>The minimum width of a stat is three columns and the maximum number of cards that can be used in a row is four.</p>
<div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-usage-layout.svg' | url }}" alt="Example of four stats in one row"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 1000px;">
    </div>

<h4>Pairing statistics with footnotes</h4>

<p>Include a footnote on the same page if you're making a claim, especially if the statistic comes from an external source. This can increase the credibility of the statistic and can better integrate the data with the page content.</p>
{% call components.example(palette='light') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-usage-with-footnote.svg' | url }}" alt="Example of a stat paired with a footnote that explains where the stat came from"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 555px;">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

{%- endcall %}

{% call components.section("Behavior") -%}

<h4 style="margin-top: -4px;">Vertical height</h4>
<p>If there are multiple stats in a row, the height of the row will be determined by the tallest stat.</p>

{% call components.example(palette='light') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-behavior-vertical-height.svg' | url }}" alt="A group of five stats arranged in two rows"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 789px;">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

{%- endcall %}

