{% call components.section("Responsive design") -%}

<h4 style="margin-top: -4px;">Large screens</h4>

<p>A single stat will span a maximum of 6 columns.</p>

    <div class="margin-bottom--7">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-responsive-desktop.svg' | url }}" alt="Example of a stat centered in a card"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 1000px;">
    </div>

<h4>Small screens</h4>

<p>Stats in a row on large screens will stack on smaller screens. Font sizes will adjust based on the <a href="/foundations/typography/">mobile typography scale</a>.</p>

    <div class="margin-bottom--7">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-responsive-mobile.svg' | url }}" alt="Three stats stacked in a 328px container with 16px margins on either side"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 360px;">
    </div>

{%- endcall %}


{% call components.section("Best practices") -%}

<h4 style="margin-top: -4px;">Including additional elements</h4>

<p>Don't use inconsistent amounts of content in stats that are grouped together.</p>

  <div class="margin-bottom--3">
    <p style="background-color: #e7f1fa; border-top: 2px solid #2b9af3; padding: 16px 16px 16px 24px; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;"><span style="color:#002952"><strong>Helpful tip</strong></span><br />A call to action does not have to appear under every stat in a group. Since it appears at the end, omitting it does not disrupt the visual flow of elements in the other stats.</p>
  </div>

{% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-best-practice-inconsistent-content.svg' | url }}" alt="Group containing a stat with icon only, stat without icon or title, and stat with title only"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 789px;" class="margin-top--2">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}


<h4>Choosing icons</h4>

<p>Don't use an icon that is unrelated to the body text.</p>

{% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-best-practice-unrelated-icon.svg' | url }}" alt="Stat about telecom companies paired with a crab icon"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 360px;">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

<h4>Title</h4>

<p>Avoid character counts that cause the title to break into two lines at any screen size.</p>

{% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-best-practice-long-title.svg' | url }}" alt="Stat with a title that wraps to two lines"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 381px;">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

<p>If a title is used for one stat in a group, write a title for each stat. Ensure the title appears in the same slot for each grouped stat to keep formatting consistent.</p>

{% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-best-practice-title-placement.svg' | url }}" alt="One row containing a stat with a title above the number, stat with no title, and stat with a title below number"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 789px;">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

<h4>Number</h4>
<p>Avoid character counts that cause the number to break into two lines at any screen size. If the number is a percentage, round up to avoid using decimals that would increase the character count.</p>

{% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-best-practice-long-number.svg' | url }}" alt="Stat with a number that wraps to two lines"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 320px;">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

<p>Avoid using 100% for more than one statistic in a group or on a page, unless you are able to cite a source and include footnotes.</p>

{% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-best-practice-100-percent-no-footnote.svg' | url }}" alt="Three stats with 100% and no footnote"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 789px;">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

<h4>Body text</h4>

<p>Keep the body text as short and consumable as possible. Be mindful of lengthy character counts, especially when stats are grouped. In general, it is not recommended to have the stat's body text span more than 5 lines on small screens.</p>

{% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-best-practice-long-body-text.svg' | url }}" alt="Stat with body text that is six lines long at mobile screen sizes"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 328px;">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}



{%- endcall %}



{% call components.section("Spacing") -%}

<h4 style="margin-top: -4px;">Within the component</h4>

<p>The Statistic component uses <a href="/foundations/spacing">spacers</a> to define space values between elements. The default and large variations use the same spacing.</p>

{% call components.example(palette='light') %}
